import java.io.{BufferedOutputStream, FileOutputStream}
import java.nio.file.{Files, Paths}

import org.apache.commons.codec.binary.Base64

object testObj extends App {
  val byteArray = Files.readAllBytes(Paths.get("C:\\Users\\siddheshj\\Desktop\\base64\\Input\\scala_basics.docx"))

  val bytesEncoded = Base64.encodeBase64(byteArray)

  val encodedStr= new String(bytesEncoded)

  println("encoded value is " + encodedStr)

  // Decode data on other side, by processing encoded data
  val valueDecoded = Base64.decodeBase64(encodedStr.getBytes());

  val bos = new BufferedOutputStream(new FileOutputStream("C:\\Users\\siddheshj\\Desktop\\base64\\Output\\test.docx"))
  Stream.continually(bos.write(valueDecoded))
  bos.close() // You may end up with 0 bytes file if not calling close.)
}




commons-codec-1.9.jar
commons-io-2.4.jar
